        2:'<span style="text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;">District Manager</span><br><span style="font-weight:bold;">Description</span>: One District Manager is authorized for each district that is active in the system. The District Manager is the single point of contact and the person responsible for all activity within their district. The District Manager can authorize Associate District Managers (ADM’s) that share the same level of privileges with the exception of being able to authorize other ADM\'s. The District Manager is also responsible for designating a single person (themselves or one of the ADM’s) that is responsible for approving new account requests that come from schools in their district.<br><span style="font-weight:bold;">Authorization</span>: The School District Superintendent, for each district that wishes to participate, must complete a District Request &amp; Authorization Form (<a href="/pdf/district_rqst_form.pdf" onmouseover="javascript:window.status=\'Download Form\'; return true" onmouseout="javascript:window.status=\'\'; return true;" class="btLBlue" style="text-decoration:underline;">click here to download</a>) that designates the person that will be the District Manager for their district. Once this document is received, the System Administrator will approve the new account request for the District Manager that has been authorized. If the District Manager needs to be changed, the Superintendent must complete a District Authorization Change Form (<a href="/pdf/district_change_form.pdf" onmouseover="javascript:window.status=\'Download Form\'; return true" onmouseout="javascript:window.status=\'\'; return true;" class="btLBlue" style="text-decoration:underline;">click here to download</a>) and send it to the System Administrator.<br><span style="font-weight:bold;">Note</span>: If you are going to be the District Manager for your school district, please proceed with this process. Your request will be sent to the System Administrator, then when your paperwork is received, your account will be enabled.',
