        6:'<span style="text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;">Case Manager</span><br><span style="font-weight:bold;">Description</span>: Case Managers are responsible for managing individual Student cases. Their duties include adding new Students as needed, preparing and completing the various forms, maintaining the Student’s team (Personnel that are allowed to view the Student’s records and add notes) and managing Parent access (they communicate user name and temporary passwords to Parents so they can access their child’s information online). The Case Manager can reset or disable Parent access if needed.<br><span style="font-weight:bold;">Authorization</span>: Case Managers are authorized by the School Manager for their school. When Case Managers add new Students, they become the Case Manager for that student by default. Case Managers cannot change the assignment of the Case Manager for a Student. Only a School Manager or ASM can do this.',
